michelleUMD Home Page

Welcome

Hi! My name is Michelle, and I'm a medical school student with interests in computer science. I'm very passionate about science, medicine, and computer science, and here I seek to explore these three interests of mine. Here's a little of what I've been up to!

If you're interested in learning to code ...

Introduction to R/RStudio

  • Coding level: beginner

  • Language: R

  • 10 lectures (~45 minutes each) taking you through the basics of R programming in application to the life sciences

Data Science Pipeline Tutorial

  • Coding level: intermediate

  • Language: Python

  • ~20-minute tutorial walking you through the steps of the Data Science Pipeline using a dataset of breast cancer surgery cases

Interactive Map Example

  • Coding level: intermediate

  • Language: Python

  • ~10-minute example of me briefly looking at the geographical distribution of arrests in the Baltimore, Maryland area on an interactive map


Ramen Data Analysis in Python

  • Coding level: beginner

  • Language: Python

  • A mini-preview for high school students on what data analysis is

  • Co-author: Sagar

Sampling of What R Can Do

  • Coding level: beginner

  • Language: R

  • Not meant to teach R, just to show a sampling of what R can do and why it would be useful for research
